Subject: RE: [VB] Crying kids and road trips- what music calms them

We had a modified version of that on our last trip to Vernal Utah. We did
our research and found enough children songs to cover the alphabet. We would
start up the session as soon as the first "are we there yet" began by saying
"what song begins with the letter "A"? Of course they may or may not have
one but we were prepared. Play the game often enough and it starts sticking
in their little heads. The littlest one couldn't play but was fascinated by
the sometimes excited competiveness around him by the other two. And they're
right. Kids can sing the same thing over and over again and never get bored.
It might drive the driver mad, but the kids are occupied.

